item.title: Manatee Sightseeing and Wildlife Boat Tour
item.description: See the gentle giants of the sea in their natural habitat on this Everglades wildlife tour. Climb aboard the covered boat and set out along the Florida waterways to spot manatees, alligators, sharks, birds, and more. Learn about the local ecosystem and wildlife from your Coast Guard-certified captain and keep your eyes peeled for manatees that sometimes come right up to the boat.

image.alt: Manatee Sightseeing and Wildlife Boat Tour

item.title: Kayak Tour Adventure Marco Island and Naples Florida
item.description: Get an up-close view of Florida’s spectacular, coastal mangrove forests—and enjoy an active way to explore—on this kayaking or paddleboarding tour. Pick from multiple tour times, head to the departure point, and meet your guide: after an introduction to your kayak or paddleboard, you’ll hit the water. Paddle through mangrove tunnels, have the chance to spot wildlife like dolphins and manatees, and learn more about the forests from your guide.

image.alt: Kayak Tour Adventure Marco Island and Naples Florida

item.title: Small Group: Saona Island Full Day Tour
item.description: Head to the sparsely inhabited Saona Island on a full-day trip from Punta Cana. Join a small group and visit the town of Mano Juan, home to a turtle conservation area. Then, spend the rest of your day exploring a secret beach as well as Abanico and Palmilla beaches, each with its own charm. Your day trip includes a simple breakfast and a hearty, buffet lunch on the beach.

image.alt: Small Group: Saona Island Full Day Tour

item.title: Marco Island Wildlife Sightseeing and Shelling Tour
item.description: Spend some time on the gulf waters of southern Florida—a nature lover's delight—on a boat tour from Marco Island to Cape Romano. With a guide, you have the chance to learn about the region's marine life and see the ecosystem of mangroves, plus go shelling.

image.alt: Marco Island Wildlife Sightseeing and Shelling Tour

item.title: Dolphin and Shelling Cruise for up to 12 people
item.description: Explore the Ten Thousand Islands by boat on a half-day tour to one of Florida’s top natural attractions. Depart from Marco Island, located just south of Naples, with a small group that is limited to 12 participants. Head to an isolated barrier island that is only accessible by boat, where you can swim in the warm waters of the Gulf of Mexico.

image.alt: Dolphin and Shelling Cruise for up to 12 people

item.title: Naples Sightseeing Boat Tour
item.description: Discover the sights and marine life of Naples on a sightseeing cruise. You have the opportunity to see birds, dolphins, and, season permitting, manatees. The cruise also takes you past the area’s top mansions, Keewaydin Island, and more. Relax and learn about local history, wildlife, and celebrity real estate during on board commentary. It’s the perfect time to take unobstructed photographs of the city and its natural surroundings.

image.alt: Naples Sightseeing Boat Tour

item.title: Manatees and Mangrove Tunnels Small Group Kayak Tour
item.description: Experience the beauty and diversity of Florida's Everglades on a kayak tour. Join a small group and paddle through mangrove forests in search of local wildlife. During the winter months, manatees can be spotted congregating in the cooler waters of deep canals. You can also observe other animals like river otters, alligators, and several bird species during your tour.

image.alt: Manatees and Mangrove Tunnels Small Group Kayak Tour

item.title: Backwater Adventure's CraigCat Tours of the 10,000 Islands
item.description: Exploring the Ten Thousand Islands National Wildlife Refuge on your own can be intimidating if you don’t know your way around on the water. Book this Thousand Islands 2-person Catamaran Tour to follow a knowledgeable guide who will keep you from getting lost and ensure you enjoy this pristine preserve to the fullest, with great opportunity to view the wildlife and sea life that inhabit the refuge.

image.alt: Backwater Adventure's CraigCat Tours of the 10,000 Islands

item.title: Mangrove Tunnels & Mudflats Kayak Tour - Local Biologist Guides
item.description: Go kayaking in the Rookery Bay Reserve on a half-day tour from Naples that is led by a local biologist guide. Learn about the wildlife and ecosystem of this stunning part of the Ten Thousand Islands in southwest Florida as you paddle through mangrove tunnels, mudflats, and oyster reefs. Look for birds and marine life such as sea stars, dolphins, large snails, and possibly even manatees.

image.alt: Mangrove Tunnels & Mudflats Kayak Tour - Local Biologist Guides

item.title: Sightseeing and Sunset Catamaran Sailing Excursion
item.description:
Set sail on this beautifully appointed Catamaran, "Cool Beans", and start making lasting memories! Cool Beans Cruises is the perfect way to see SW Florida, By Water! Choose from a 2.5 hr. Day-Sail or a 2 hr. Champagne Sunset Cruise. With quick access to the Gulf of Mexico, you will experience true sailing with limited motoring. A stop for a swim to a secluded pristine beach for shelling can be part of the Day Sail Only(weather permitting). Keep your cameras ready to capture a photo of the local wildlife to see along the way! Cool Beans Catamaran will accommodate up to 20 passengers. PRICE INCLUDES SODA, WATER, BEER, & WHITE WINE . A CHAMPAGNE TOAST AT SUNSET IS INCLUDED FOR THE SUNSET CRUISE. Please note that parties of 7 or more, an 18% gratuity is added to our base price and is due and payable to the Captain.
Also available is our 25 Ft .Pontoon, Lil' Beans! Perfect for up close eco/nature /shelling and island hopping. Book a Private tour for a group for up to 6 guests

image.alt: Sightseeing and Sunset Catamaran Sailing Excursion

item.title: Guided Island EcoTour: CLEAR/Standard Kayak, SUP - Bonita Springs
item.description:
Experience the natural beauty and marine life of Southwest Florida up-close with a CLEAR kayak! Don't just take our word on what an awesome tour this is... see our TripAdvisor Travelers' Choice Awards for 2022 and 2023! Paddle Naples' tours are in the top 10% of all worldwide tours!
Our Five-Star guided eco-tours and rentals take you through Estero Bay and the Gulf of Mexico’s most incredible paddling routes... including mangrove tunnels, secluded beaches, and prime shelling areas! This is prime habitat for dolphins (year round) and manatees (mostly warm water months).
We use top quality standard kayaks and paddleboards that are comfortable and easy to paddle. We have CLEAR paddleboards too, and HOBIE pedal kayaks if needed.
Complementary photos included!
Looking for something truly unique? Try our CLEAR Kayak Sunset Glow Tour. We will paddle to a secluded beach for shelling until sunset, then we turn on the colorful underwater LED lights and have a great time paddling back!

image.alt: Guided Island EcoTour: CLEAR/Standard Kayak, SUP - Bonita Springs

item.title: Marco Island Dolphin Sightseeing Tour
item.description: Look for dolphins in the waters of the Ten Thousand Islands on this boat tour from Marco Island. With a captain-guide, explore a piece of Florida's gulf coast to see and learn about the natural environment. You also have the opportunity to spot shorebirds with your live guide on hand to identify them.

image.alt: Marco Island Dolphin Sightseeing Tour

item.title: Avi's Premium Dolphin Tour by Jet Ski
item.description: Get on a jetski and have an adventure while you explore the mangroves of Cape Romano and the 10,000 Islands of Marco Island, on a dolphin tour. You’ll also spot manatees, all sorts of birds, and sea turtles. Two people can ride on each jetski (max 400lbs), so that is double the fun. Note that if born after Jan 1, 1988, the rider must take a boat test (additional cost).

image.alt: Avi's Premium Dolphin Tour by Jet Ski

item.title: Gulf of Mexico Sunset Cruise from Naples
item.description: Cruise aboard the Double Sunshine from Naples and into the Gulf of Mexico at sunset. Move freely on the deck to see the best views and capture lovely pictures. You may be able to spot dolphins or manatees swimming in the gulf. Cruise past stunning mansions in exclusive Port Royal, serene Keewaydin Island, and enjoy the tales of Florida history from your knowledgeable captain.

image.alt: Gulf of Mexico Sunset Cruise from Naples

item.title: Marco Island 2 hour Dolphin, Birding and Shelling tour
item.description: Discover some of coastal Florida's loveliest scenery, and its wealth of wildlife, on this small-group tour of the Ten Thousand Islands National Wildlife Refuge from Marco Island. Pick from several daily departure times, and set off with just a small group for company. Go on a naturalist-guided boat tour to spot animals like dolphins, pelicans, spoonbills, manatees, sea turtles, and more. Then, disembark at an uninhabited barrier island for a shelling expedition.

image.alt: Marco Island 2 hour Dolphin, Birding and Shelling tour

item.title: Small Group Motorboat Eco Tour of the Everglades
item.description: Explore the Everglades and discover the stunning range of animals living in this unique ecosystem on this intimate tour. On this small-group tour, there’s no need to clamber over the heads and shoulders of other tourists to catch a glimpse of this shallow-water area’s native residents – including fish, birds, sea turtles, manatees, and maybe even bottlenose dolphins. Disembark on an isolated island during the tour and enjoy the serenity of this unique nature tour.

image.alt: Small Group Motorboat Eco Tour of the Everglades

item.title: 3 Hour Guided Mangrove Tunnel Kayak Eco Tour
item.description: Discover the exotic beauty of the Everglades’ mangrove forest on a kayaking eco-tour. Spend time winding through sleepy creeks and under mangrove canopies, getting up-close views of resident herons, alligators, ducks, otters and more. With a professional naturalist guide, learn kayaking technique and enjoy exploring this unusual wetlands setting.

image.alt: 3 Hour Guided Mangrove Tunnel Kayak Eco Tour

item.title: Clear Kayak Guided Eco Tour in North Naples
item.description: CLEAR KAYAKING! Join us for an adventure in the scenic area of Wiggins Pass in Naples. We'll enjoy spectacular views of the Gulf of Mexico, Barefoot Beach Preserve and Delnor-Wiggins State Park. We'll kayak through mangroves and take photos along the way. Be on the lookout for dolphins, manatees and other local wildlife.

image.alt: Clear Kayak Guided Eco Tour in North Naples

item.title: CityTour La Paz, Balandra beach and the Magic Town of Todos Santos
item.description: Discover La Paz with our exciting tour: history in every corner, impressive views, free time to explore and photographs. Immerse yourself in the vibrant coastal atmosphere and enjoy delicious local cuisine. A carefully curated tour for an authentic experience.

image.alt: CityTour La Paz, Balandra beach and the Magic Town of Todos Santos

item.location: San Jose del Cabo, Los Cabos

item.title: Guided Kayak Mangrove Ecotour in Rookery Bay Reserve, Naples
item.description: Explore Rookery Bay National Estuarine Research Reserve in Naples on an ecotour by kayak. Following a guide, you'll paddle across the waters of the bay, part of the Ten Thousand Islands, for an up-close look at the mangrove forest. Watch for birds and other marine life on this tour suitable for beginner and advanced kayakers.

image.alt: Guided Kayak Mangrove Ecotour in Rookery Bay Reserve, Naples

item.title: Ten Thousand Island Jet Ski Eco Tour - Marco Island
item.description: Take a break from the beach on a Jet Ski tour through the waters of Ten Thousand Islands. In addition to pointing out dolphins and sea creatures often missed by untrained eyes, your guide brings you to secluded locations inaccessible to boats or kayaks. With a range of departure times, this adventure is a popular choice for visitors to Naples.

image.alt: Ten Thousand Island Jet Ski Eco Tour - Marco Island

item.title: Eco Shelling Cruise to Keewaydin Island
item.description: Nature lovers can spend a day immersed in pristine landscapes on this shelling cruise from Naples, Florida to Keewaydin Island. Join a small group and board your vessel for the journey to the remote island. Cruise past mangrove forests and see wildlife such as alligators, dolphins, and even manatees along the way. Once you reach Keewaydin, take a nature walk and fill your big with beach treasures before heading back.

image.alt: Eco Shelling Cruise to Keewaydin Island

item.title: Private Shelling and Dolphin Excursion
item.description: Southwest Florida is a shell collector’s paradise. With ten thousand islands filling the area of the Gulf off of Marco Island, a private shelling tour is a great way to enjoy time under the Florida sun. Explore remote islands during this relaxed tour. Board a boat and sail to the secluded areas off of Marco Island where you’ll stroll the white sands in search of remarkable shells. As you sail, expect to see dolphins playing in the waves.

image.alt: Private Shelling and Dolphin Excursion

item.title: Guided Hobie Kayak EcoTour: Premium Eco Experience Bonita Springs
item.description: Explore the waters around Bonita Springs in your own Hobie kayak with a local guide on this group tour. Visit a beach and look out for wild dolphins, manatees, and coastal birds as your guide shares their local knowledge with you. They will also help you get the best photographs of you, your family, and the wildlife, free of charge.

image.alt: Guided Hobie Kayak EcoTour: Premium Eco Experience Bonita Springs
